<br>
Bruiser the bartender looks up from his latest concoction, some froglok tongue swill, for the ogre in the corner.  With an acknowledging look in his eyes, the bartender nods his bald head at the newly arrived patrons.  Anders and his companions head to an empty table near the back of the room.<br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
This is not the safest part of town, and Bruiser’s Tavern (as I call it) has quite a reputation for gathering some of the most feared/respected adventurers in Norrath good and evil.  One would think the city guard would have a garrison patrolling this place due to some of the patrons who frequent here.<br>
<br>
But the powerful rogue guild owns and runs Bruiser's place, and I am not one to say where he stands in the heirarchy of things.  Bruiser and I go way back, that is all I can say.  <br>
<br>
Most who come here know better then to start conflict in an establishment operated by such a powerful faction.  <br>
<br>
An occasional few who have crossed over the line were later found dead, slumped over in some back ally, or just never seen again.<br>
<br>
My comrades and I are here to collect information about the 3rd part of the Chardok Ring quest.  From previous conversation, Bruiser tipped me off that a gnome who has been ‘in’ lately is allies with the Sarnaks.  I plan to dip into that well.<br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
Immediately upon sitting down, a short human woman, a bit plump around the waist, with a pretty face and full lips, stops at our table and with a flirtatious smile asks what we would like.<br>
<br>
<br>
