<br>
Sinadwen shrugged, not even taking his eyes from the tome on the table in front of him. A single candle stood on the tabletop between them, lighting the map and book. &quot;Hugging trees?&quot; he muttered, turning a page.<br>
<br>
&quot;Bah. You're useless. Tell the others I'll be back,&quot; the Priestess grumbled, causing a silver brow to inch into Sinadwen's forehead as he peaked up from his book. <br>
<br>
Isharra closed the door behind her, sending a gust of chilly air at Sinadwen, extinguishing his candle. &quot;Blasted cleric,&quot; he muttered, then just sat back in his chair in the darkness.<br>
