<br>
*After closing the door with another push from my boot, and placing down the last box, I glance around, drawing back the hood from my head, revealling a shaved head and brilliant emerald eyes, both of which reflect the firelight.*<br>
<br>
*Despite the tiny icicles that have gathered on my short dark beard, a warm smile appears*<br>
<br>
Oi, Bruiser, 'ere are ya muffins lad. Yer lucky Poppyseed is such ah dear tha she let me out in tha storm.<br>
<br>
*I arrange the boxes of muffins safely off to one side, then take a seat up at the bar.*<br>
<br>
One ov those &quot;warm chocolates&quot; er &quot;hot cocoas&quot; er wotever ya call them please.<br>
<br>
*I grin a look of &quot;thanks&quot; as Im given a giant steaming mug of cocoa, which I immediately raise to my lips, savoring the sweet, warm, mixture as I would a kiss, though a kiss from my beloved would warm me far more than a drink ever could. I then turn around to scan the room over the rim of my mug.*<br>
<br>
Buran McMuffin, the original Iron Chef<br>
