 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uburanmcmuffin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BuranMcMuffin</A> at: 6/21/02 5:23:53 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uisharramoonsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Isharra Moonsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/21/02 5:23:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=79.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~brennec/_uimages/Isharra.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Out of Place</span><hr size=1> Isharra comes to a stop outside of the tavern, looking around warily at the shadowy streets and checking the little brown book in her hand to make sure she was at the right place. Closing the book with a frown, she tucks it back into its secret place, hoping that Gatsu was correct in his guess of Anders whereabouts. She should have brought the warrior with her, she realizes now, but she hadn't told him that she was actually going to hunt the ranger down, and he'd seemed too busy polishing his armor to go for a walk.<br>
<br>
The cowl of her cloak is pulled up far over her Koada'Dal features, lest someone notice just how out of place she is here. She checks the purse at her belt to make sure it is still tightly fastened and then enters the tavern.<br>
<br>
The sounds of merry-making and the smells of booze and halfling tabac waft toward her as she lets the door close softly behind her. A few people look her way, but no one seems very interested in the new arrival. She breathes a sigh of relief and scans the crowd for Anders.<br>
<br>
A seedy bunch, they are, and some of them very obviously intoxicated. A dwarf at a nearby table belches loudly and Isharra wrinkles her nose, glad that the cowl hides her obvious disgust. <br>
<br>
Finally her eyes fall upon her prey. The ranger sits at a table with two companions, but their backs are to her. She approaches the table quickly and nudges Anders, her jade eyes peering down at him from beneath the cowl. Surprise dawns on his face as she speaks. &quot;By the gods, ranger! You keep shady company!&quot; she whispers, then turns to nod at his companions, adding, &quot;Present company excepted, of course....&quot;<br>
 <p><i>Isharra Moonsong</i><BR>
<i>Priestess of Tunare</i><br>
