**Slayin gnolls n makin muffins since 3174** <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uburanmcmuffin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BuranMcMuffin</A> at: 7/1/02 7:45:55 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaritzia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maritzia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Uptight Cleric</span><br>  Posts: 320<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 12:52:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=79.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Out of Place</span><hr size=1> Maritzia stumbles in and makes her way to the bar, pounding for service and yelling for a bottle of brandy.  She had spent the better part of the last week invissed in parts of Freeport she'd never known existed before.  The things she'd seen and heard still turned her stomach.  She'd stopped at every bar and pub on the way home, hoping the drink would erase some of the vile images from her mind.<br>
<br>
It hadn't...<br>
<br>
 <p>Maritzia Soulhealer<br>
29th Season Cleric of Rodcet Nife<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umidwestpatriot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MidwestPatriot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 159<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 4:33:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=79.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Out of Place</span><hr size=1> I was taken aback by the sight of my dear friend Isharra.  I studied her attractive and mischevious face before standing to give her a hug.  After standing I paused first, remembering the warning... and glance over to my mage friend, Ealenye, sitting across from my chair.  Ealenye nods her head, and I turn back to give Isharra a hug.<br>
<br>
Isharra saw this and quickly pushed me away.  <br>
<br>
&quot;What is this Anders?!  Can you not even give your friend a hug without <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    permission</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> from this other woman?&quot;  <br>
<br>
Isharra noded her head in the direction of Ealenye while making strong eye contact with her.<br>
<br>
Ealenye smiled back, which seemed to not help the situation.<br>
 <br>
&quot;You have changed much, foolish elf, if you do not have the ability to make your own decisions.&quot;<br>
<br>
A rolling laugh erupted out of my chest, quickly drowned out by the myriad of noises in the tavern.  I saw the consternation in Isharras face, but I could not contain my smile.<br>
<br>
<br>
I decide to forgo a hug from Isharra, and motioned her to one of the open chairs at our table.<br>
<br>
&quot;Please have a seat Isharra, we have much to talk about.  Ealenye has been casting identify on everyone we meet.  We have encountered a couple imposters these last few days.  People disguised with magic who resemble friends,family... but have other intentions...&quot;  <br>
<br>
I looked over to Turin.  Turin a ranger friend, sat quietly, his mind seemingly lost in thought, as he nurtured his 3rd mug of heated Dain's Porter.  A silvertipped arrow rested on the table next to his arm where he had been examining its features just moments before.<br>
<br>
I started, &quot;Yesterday we were met by a woman masquerading as Turin's sister.  She was very convincing.  Turin met her while he was out scouting and brought her back to our camp unaware of the danger.  She was feigning fatigue and slight illness.  No sooner then she was within all of our presence, and Ealenye was preoccupied with scribing some spell, Turin's sister attacked us unaware.  <br>
<br>
Just as the imposter was about to stab Ealenye from behind, Turin from the edge of camp, quickly noticed the danger and at the last second shot an arrow through her head.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Curious about Turin's reaction to my retelling of the previous day's events, I again looked over to him.<br>
<br>
Turin acted as if he had not just heard my retelling of the incident.  His eyes were fixed on his mug and the wisp of steam coming out of it.  I knew he felt bad for bringing the danger back to the camp, threatening the lives of his party.  And he felt foolish for being duped.  We forgave him for it.  It wasn't his fault.  Magic is hard to detect.  I think he was unnerved for killing something which resembled his sister.  For after we inspected the corpse, we found it to be some daemon-like thing.  Death revealed it's true form.  <br>
<br>
Just as I was about to again insist Isharra have a seat and join us at the table, a whisper in my right ear from behind me caught me by surprise.  Phaedrax's sweet voice greeted me, as I spun around planting a kiss on her cheek.<br>
<br>
&quot;Blessed Tunare, everyone is sneaking up on me today!&quot;  I announced.  &quot;I need to slow down on my drinks&quot;, I said as I looked down at my half-full pint of lager.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Plus,&quot; I said, &quot;with all of the commotion in here...it's a sensory overload.&quot;  <br>
<br>
I looked to the next table over, where two barbarians were shouting at eachother in drunken slurs, apparently in disagreement over which of them killed more goblins the night before.<br>
<br>
Music played in the background.  It was a twisted barrage of sound, almost eerie.  From where I stood the different tunes floated from numerous tables.  The songs and voices intertwined with eachother, only the closest taking slight dominance over the others...songs telling tales of victorious conquests and fallen comrades.  Some were fast and upbeat, while others were slow, drumming, and ominous.  Through all the clamor, its surprising we were able to keep our sanity.<br>
<br>
I embraced my friend Phaedrax saying, &quot;I am so happy you made it.  Was your man able to come too?&quot;<br>
<br>
Ealenye said with a smirk on her face, &quot;I saw each of them approaching, not all of us are as oblivious to our surroundings as you Anders.&quot;<br>
<br>
I stuck my tongue out at Ealenye, with a bit of a smile and turned back to Isharra, still standing where I left her.  <br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><b><i><font color = "purple">Anders Silverblade</font><font color = "darkblue"> the Vagabond Ranger </font><br><font color = "silver"><a href="http://www.guildportal.com/guildHome.asp?GuildID=1158">Band of Dreamers</a></font></i></b><br><br>
<font color = "silver" size = "2"><i>…Drifters' gold is for me to spend for I am a vagabond…All that I see is mine to keep. Foolish, the fancy seems. But I am rich with the wealth of sight. The coin of the realm of dreams…"</i>
</font>
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umidwestpatriot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MidwestPatriot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/25/02 8:39:07 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uisharramoonsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Isharra Moonsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/3/02 9:06:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=79.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~brennec/_uimages/Isharra.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Discovered</span><hr size=1> &quot;Indeed,&quot; Isharra replied, not happy at all to be subjected to the mage's scrutiny. She nodded at Turin and Phaedrax, her eyes smiling in recognition, though the rest of her features were ice. She did not even give the mage a glance. &quot;Yes, I know Phaedrax, and I had the pleasure . . . or something like that . . . of meeting Turin last evening,&quot; she said softly, offering Turin a small smile. She liked the ranger, even if he was a bit eccentric. She was just not accustomed to his roughness, and she had been startled when Turin, in wolf form, lifted his leg and wet Xaviar's robes. But Turin was clever and friendly, even if his behavior was scandalous.<br>
<br>
Refusing to make herself comfortable in a place where she did not intend to stay, Isharra turned to Anders, looking increasingly uncomfortable in her surroundings. &quot;I won't take but a moment of your time, ranger&quot; she said coolly, removing a map from within her cloak and placing it on the table. &quot;I need you to show me the precise location of where we set up camp the last time we visited Mistmoore.&quot; For a moment, the cleric's lofty demeanor is shaken as she swallows uncomfortably, uncertainty and embarrassment flashing through her eyes. &quot;I misplaced,&quot; she pauses to weigh her words, &quot;... something .... and I think it might be there somewhere. I intend to fetch it, once you point me in the right direction.&quot; Anders's eyes widen with surprise and he opens his mouth to speak but is interrupted when Isharra is thrust forward over the table by a staggering dwarf's misstep. Booze and ale splashes everywhere, drenching the party's laps and ruining the map. Isharra's face is the color of beets as she struggles to right herself, and the hood of her cloak falls to her shoulders, revealing her delicate features and pale, porcelin skin. <br>
<br>
Around them, the crowd breaks out in peals of laughter, and the drunken dwarf blinks slowly, staring blankly at the high elf until he finally says, &quot;Oh, zhear me, sho shorry, m'lazhy...&quot; Bread crumbs and cheese dangle in his bristly red beard, and his bald head glows in the firelight. &quot;Here, letch me help zhou,&quot; he slurs, groping out to take her hand... and pinching her bottom instead! <br>
<br>
